      "writtenOn": "2026-05-07T14:02:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "why not write the entire path string? it feels to me like writing the selectors without separators is dangerous, e.g. `foo.barbaz` and `foobar.baz` would hash the same if we don\u0027t include any separator.\n\nalso, is there some sort of hasher interface we could add to the path or selector types, so that they can write their contents to a hasher without the stringify step?",
